This paper deals with the fundamental tradeoff between data rate and reliability in a slow fading channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The specific channel being studied is the interference channel, which is a type of networked communication system (cs.NI). The paper also discusses coding schemes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of computer engineering (cs.CE) and multimedia (cs.MM) due to its focus on communication systems.
